<html>
  <head>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Montserrat:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <meta charset="UTF-8">

    <style>
      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: black;
        overflow-x: hidden;
      }

      .scroll {
        height: 400vh;
      }

      .camera {
        position: fixed;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100vh;
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .world {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        will-change: transform;
      }

      .base {
        width: 100%;
        display: block;
      }

      .overlay {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        width: 100%;
        opacity: 0;
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      .veil {
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0;
        background: black;
        opacity: 0;
        pointer-events: none;
        z-index: 5;
      }

      .menu {
  position: fixed;
  top: 18px;
  left: 28px;

  z-index: 20;

  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-start;
  align-items: center;

  gap: 28px;

  font-family: "Montserrat", Arial, sans-serif;

  font-size: 28px;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;

  color: rgba(240,240,240,0.78);
  mix-blend-mode: difference;

  pointer-events: auto;
}

.menu a {
  color: inherit;
  text-decoration: none;
  opacity: 1.0;
  transition: opacity 200ms ease, transform 200ms ease;
}

.menu a:hover {
  opacity: 0.5;
  transform: translateY(-1px);
}
.menu a.active {
  opacity: 1;
  border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor;
  padding-bottom: 2px;
}
   .menu-vignette {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100vw;
  height: 120px;
  z-index: 15;
  pointer-events: none;

  background: linear-gradient(
  to bottom,
  rgba(0,0,0,0.90) 0%,
  rgba(0,0,0,0.75) 25%,
  rgba(0,0,0,0.50) 55%,
  rgba(0,0,0,0.25) 80%,
  rgba(0,0,0,0.00) 100%
);

  -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(
    to bottom,
    rgba(0,0,0,1) 0%,
    rgba(0,0,0,1) 65%,
    rgba(0,0,0,0) 100%
  );

  mask-image: linear-gradient(
    to bottom,
    rgba(0,0,0,1) 0%,
    rgba(0,0,0,1) 65%,
    rgba(0,0,0,0) 100%
  );
}

  .text-panel {
  position: fixed;
  top: 50%;
  right: 24vw;
  left: auto;
  transform: translateY(-50%);

  width: 900px;
  max-width: 85vw;

  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 50px;
  flex-direction: row-reverse;

  text-align: right;


  font-family: "Montserrat", Arial, sans-serif;
  font-weight: 300;

        color: rgba(240,240,240,0.95);
        font-size: 22px;
        line-height: 1.6;

        opacity: 0;
        pointer-events: none;
        z-index: 10;

        transition: opacity 220ms ease;
      }
      .notebook {
  position: relative;

  width: min(22vw, 260px);
  height: auto;

  flex-shrink: 0;

  opacity: 1;

  pointer-events: none;

  transition: opacity 220ms ease;
}
}

  pointer-events: none;

  transition: opacity 220ms ease;
}

.text-content {
  position: relative;
}

      .text-title {
        font-size: 32px;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

#glitch-layer {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;

  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;

  pointer-events: none;
  z-index: 2;
}


.glitch-img {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;

  width: 100%;
  height: auto;

  display: block;

  opacity: 0;
  mix-blend-mode: difference;

  animation: glitchFlash 500ms ease-out forwards;
}

      @keyframes glitchFlash {
  0% {
    opacity: 0;
  }

  15% {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  60% {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  100% {
    opacity: 0;
  }
}
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>

    <div class="menu-vignette" id="menuVignette"></div>

    <div class="menu">
    <a href="/"class="active">The&nbsp;Folded&nbsp;Map</a>
      <a href="/about">About</a>
      <a href="/media">Media</a>
      <a href="/research">Research</a>
    </div>

    <div class="scroll"></div>

    <div class="camera">

      <div class="world" id="world">

  <div id="glitch-layer"></div>

  <img class="base" id="baseImage" src="/Mess.jpg" />

  <img class="overlay" id="music" src="/Music-Doodles.png" />
  <img class="overlay" id="philosophy" src="/Philosophy-Doodles.png" />
  <img class="overlay" id="art" src="/Art-Doodles.png" />
  <img class="overlay" id="science" src="/Science-Doodles.png" />

</div>

      <div class="veil" id="veil"></div>

    </div>

    <div class="text-panel" id="text-music">

  <img class="notebook" src="/Notebook-Music.png">
  
      
      The Folded Map is a project about Renaissance polyphony. And yet it is also 
      about philosophy, art and science. It’s the claim that polyphonic music is 
      part of the world, part of knowledge and inextricably bound to the histories we inhabit. 

    
    </div>

    <div class="text-panel" id="text-philosophy">
      
       <img class="notebook" src="/Notebook-Philosophy.png">

With a map we may wander, evade cul-de-sacs and hunt for treasure. A map is a provisional thing, 
reflecting the varied topologies of each time and place. And so it depicts not terrain as such, but our 
circuitous attempts to parse it, to navigate it and to know it. This is its true territory.
      
    


    </div>

    <div class="text-panel" id="text-art">

    <img class="notebook" src="/Notebook-Art.png">
      
      Polyphonic compositions also toy with terrain, staging and exploring that gap between 
      representation and actuality. They behave like conceptual art, commenting upon the conditions 
      of creation and their own perilous reception. 
    </div>

    <div class="text-panel" id="text-science">

    <img class="notebook" src="/Notebook-Science.png">
      
       Seeing polyphony as a map, is to hear an age of discovery—visual, geographic 
       and scientific. It means positioning these works within a “paradigm shift”, one that upended what 
       was untimately knowable, and how we see our arts, and ourselves, in realtion to the unknown.
    </div>

    <script>
      const ids = ["music", "philosophy", "art", "science"];
      const textIds = ["text-music", "text-philosophy", "text-art", "text-science"];

      const world = document.getElementById("world");
      const veil = document.getElementById("veil");
      const baseImage = document.getElementById("baseImage");
const menuVignette = document.getElementById("menuVignette");

function syncGlitchHeight() {
  document.querySelectorAll(".glitch-img").forEach(img => {
    img.style.height = baseImage.offsetHeight + "px";
  });
}

window.addEventListener("resize", syncGlitchHeight);

      const anchors = [0.20, 0.40, 0.60, 0.80];

      function clamp01(x) {
        return Math.max(0, Math.min(1, x));
      }

      function smooth(x) {
        return x * x * (3 - 2 * x);
      }

      function getT() {
        const scrollY = window.scrollY;
        const maxScroll = document.body.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
        if (maxScroll <= 0) return 0;
        return scrollY / maxScroll;
      }

      function updateCamera(t) {
        const y = t * (baseImage.offsetHeight - window.innerHeight);
        world.style.transform = `translateY(${-y}px)`;
      }

      function weight(i, t) {
        const dist = Math.abs(t - anchors[i]);
        const range = 0.18;
        return clamp01(1 - dist / range);
      }

      function update() {
        const t = getT();

        updateCamera(t);

        textIds.forEach((id, i) => {
          const el = document.getElementById(id);
          const w = weight(i, t);
          const visible = w > 0.35 ? (w - 0.35) / 0.65 : 0;
          el.style.opacity = clamp01(visible);
        });

        const shift = 0.22;
        const falloff = 1.4;

        ids.forEach((id, i) => {
          const el = document.getElementById(id);
          let w = weight(i, t);
          w = Math.max(0, w - shift);
          w = Math.pow(w, 1 / falloff);
          el.style.opacity = w * 0.95;
        });

        const fadeInEnd = 0.18;
        const fadeOutStart = 0.82;

        let dim = 0;

        if (t < fadeInEnd) {
          dim = smooth(t / fadeInEnd);
        } else if (t > fadeOutStart) {
          dim = smooth((1 - t) / (1 - fadeOutStart));
        } else {
          dim = 1;
        }

        veil.style.opacity = dim * 0.82;
      }

      function loop() {
        update();
        requestAnimationFrame(loop);
      }

      loop();

      const glitchLayer = document.getElementById("glitch-layer");

function syncGlitchSize() {
  glitchLayer.style.height = baseImage.offsetHeight + "px";
}

baseImage.onload = syncGlitchSize;
syncGlitchSize();

window.addEventListener("resize", syncGlitchSize);

const glitchImages = [
  "glitch1.png",
  "glitch2.png",
  "glitch3.png",
  "glitch4.png"
];

let lastGlitch = null;

function getRandomGlitch() {
  let next;

  do {
    next = glitchImages[Math.floor(Math.random() * glitchImages.length)];
  } while (next === lastGlitch);

  lastGlitch = next;
  return next;
}

function spawnGlitch() {
  const img = document.createElement("img");

  img.src = getRandomGlitch();
  img.className = "glitch-img";

  glitchLayer.appendChild(img);

  syncGlitchHeight();

  setTimeout(() => {
    img.remove();
  }, 180);
}

      function glitchCycle() {
        spawnGlitch();
        const next = Math.random() * (1200 - 300) + 300;
        setTimeout(glitchCycle, next);
      }

      glitchCycle();
    </script>

  </body>
</html>